Final: No. 13 Virginia 7, Liberty 4

#UVa is 33-9 overall, and have snapped their three-game losing streak. 

Anthony Stephan was 2-for-3 with two doubles, two RBI and two runs. Evan Blanco earned the win, having provided two scoreless innings of relief and five strikeouts.

Bottom 8: #UVa 7, Liberty 4

Cavaliers add another run on Anthony Stephan's RBI double to right field. He's had an excellent night.

Top 8: #UVa 6, Liberty 4

Hoos freshman reliever Evan Blanco walks off to a nice ovation from the crowd at The Dish. He struck out five of the six batters he faced and more importantly didn't allow the Cavs' deficit to grow after replacing starter Connelly Early in the sixth.

Bottom 7: #UVa 6, Liberty 4

Griff O'Ferrall's base hit sends Stephan and Godbout home to put the Hoos in front.

Bottom 7: Liberty 4, #UVa 4

Henry Godbout's two-run single evens the score. Hoos needed that.

Bottom 7: Liberty 4, #UVa 2

Anthony Stephan's bases-loaded walk brings the Hoos within two. Cavaliers still have the bases full. One out.

Bottom 6: Liberty 4, #UVa 1

Griff O'Ferrall's infield single scores Anthony Stephan to get the Hoos on the board.

Bottom 6: Liberty 4, #UVa 0

Anthony Stephan's double down the right-field line gives the Cavaliers their first hit and breaks up the perfect game Liberty had going.

Top 6: Liberty 4, #UVa 0 

Gray Betts' second RBI single extends the Flames' lead and Cam Foster's two-run single grows their advantage even larger. Connelly Early, who was so good through the first five frames, will exit with two outs in the sixth.

End 5: Liberty 1, #UVa 0 

Flames left fielder Kane Kepley with one of the great catches of the season. Jumped and robbed Ethan Anderson of a would-be home run, keeping the Cavaliers hitless.

Mid 5: Liberty 1, #UVa 0

Cavaliers starter Connelly Early up to seven strikeouts.

End 4: Liberty 1, #UVa 0

The first 12 hitters for the Cavaliers have been retired.

Mid 4: Liberty 1, #UVa 0

Flames go ahead on Gray Betts' RBI single that sent Brayden Horton across the plate. Horton reached on an infield single and advanced to second on a throwing error by Jake Gelof.

End 3: Scoreless

#UVa starter Connelly Early has retired seven straight hitters and has yielded only one hit. Liberty starter Trey Cooper has retired the first nine he's faced.
